description: A special placeholder value used to specify "gaps" within functions, allowing partial application of any combination of arguments.

name: isNothing
description: Returns true if the value under test is empty or nil.
examples:
isNothing(undefined) //=> true
       isNothing(null) //=> true
       isNothing([]) //=> true
       isNothing('') //=> true
       isNothing({}) //=> true
       isNothing('Hello, world!') //=> false

name: isEqualTo
description: Returns true if the 2 provided values are deeply equal.

name: testRegex
description: Returns booleon based upon provided regex.
examples:
testRegex('Batman', 'Bruce Wayne') //=> false
       testRegex(/Batman/i, 'batman Wayne') //=> true

name: isLessThan
description: Returns true if the second value is less than the first value.

name: isGreaterThan
description: Returns true if the second value is greater than the first value.

name: isLessThanEqualTo
description: Returns true if the second value is less than or equal to the first value.

name: isGreaterThanEqualTo
description: Returns true if the second value is greater than or equal to the first value.

name: identity
description: A function that returns the same value it was passed.

name: add
examples:
add(2, 2) //=> 4
        add(2, '2') //=> 4
        add(2, null) //=> 2
        add(undefined, null) //=> 0

name: subtract
examples:
subtract(4, 2) //=> 2
        subtract(4, '2') //=> 2
        subtract(4, null) //=> 4
        subtract(undefined, null) //=> 0

name: multiply
examples:
multiply(4, 2) //=> 8
        multiply(4, '2') //=> 8
        multiply(4, null) //=> 0
        multiply(undefined, null) //=> 0

name: divide
examples:
divide(4, 2) //=> 2
        divide(4, '2') //=> 2
        divide(4, null) //=> 4
        divide(undefined, null) //=> 0

name: max
examples:
max(4, 2) //=> 4
        max(4, '2') //=> 4
        max(4, null) //=> 4
        max(undefined, null) //=> 0

name: min
examples:
min(4, 2) //=> 2
        min(4, '2') //=> 2
        min(4, null) //=> 0
        min(undefined, null) //=> 0

name: makePair
description: Returns `[x, y]`.

name: pickFrom
description:
Retrieves value at the specified path from a JSON object. '*' in the path is regarded as
a wildcard, meaning anything at this level will used to pick value from.

name: pickByRegex
description: Filters key-value pairs from a JSON object when key matches the specified regular expression (or string).

name: mergeWithAdd
description: Merges a list of JSON objects into a single JSON object by adding values having the same key; treats a non-number value as zero.

name: mergeWithSubtract
description: Merges a list of JSON objects into a single JSON object by subtracting values having the same key; treats a non-number value as zero.
examples: mergeWithSubtract([{ a: 1, b: 5 }, { a: 2 }, { a: 3 }]) //=> { a: 2, b: 5 }

name: mergeWithMax
description: Merges a list of JSON objects into a single JSON object by applying max to values having the same key; treats a non-number value as zero.

name: mergeWithMin
description: Merges a list of JSON objects into a single JSON object by applying min to values having the same key; treats a non-number value as zero.

name: mergeAll
description: Merges a list of JSON objects into a single JSON object by subtracting values having the same key; treats a non-number value as zero.

name: differential
description: Applies iterative subtraction over consecutive values in a JSON object such that T[i] = T[i] - T[i-1]; first value is ignored in the result.
examples: differential({ a: 1, b: 2, c: 3 }) //=> { b: 1, c: 1 }

name: sumAll
description:
Recieves an array or object, adds all the values and return a single number. All non-number values
are treated as zero.

name: defaultAll
description:
Recieves an array or object and replaces each junky value with the provided fallback value.
A value is considered junk if it can not be converted to a valid number. A stringy number
is converted to number.

name: getUsedMemory
description: Calculates percentages of used memory when given a list or JSON object containing percentages of free memory.

name: getAvg
description: Calculates average of values in a list or JSON object; ignores values that are not numbers.

name: runAll
description:
Execute a list of pipelines on provided data. A pipeline is an array of action descriptions.
An action can be described in form of a string or JSON.

name: getRate
description: Divides values in a list or JSON object by the provided denominator.

name: map
description: Takes an action and data as input and returns the result of performing that action on each value in the data.

name: _sort
description:
Sort an Object or Array. Type can either be 'ascend' or 'descend'. When data is an array of
objects or arrays, key refers to the value with respect to which you want the data sorted. When data is an
object, key can either be `0` (sort by key) or `1` (sort by value); sorted object is returned as
a list of `[key, value]` pairs. When data is simply an array of numbers, key is ignored even if provided.

name: sortAscending
description:
Sorts an array or object in ascending order. When data is an array of objects or arrays, key
refers to the value with respect to which you want the data sorted. When data is an object, key
can either be `0` (sort by key) or `1` (sort by value); sorted object is returned as a list
of `[key, value]` pairs. When data is simply an array of numbers, key is ignored even if provided.

name: sortDescending
description:
Sorts an array or object in descending order. When data is an array of objects or arrays, key
refers to the value with respect to which you want the data sorted. When data is an object, key
can either be `0` (sort by key) or `1` (sort by value); sorted object is returned as a list
of `[key, value]` pairs. When data is simply an array of numbers, key is ignored even if provided.

name: cleanData
description:
Removes values from an array or object by applying the provided predicate functions on
each value in an OR fashion. Additionally for an object, if a key is empty, it is removed
regardless of the value.

name: cleanDataByKeys
description: Removes values from an array or object by applying provided predicate on keys or indices.

name: takeTopAndCombineOthers
description:
Takes top `x` items from a list and combines remaining by applying provided xformer.
Returns `[...topX, others]`.

name: takeTopPairsAndAddOthers
description:
Takes top `x` pairs from a list of pairs and combines remaining pairs by adding values
on index `1` of each pair; a pair should be of form `[x: any, y: number]`. Returns `[topX, others]`.

name: getMax
description: Find max value.

name: any
description: Check if any value in array or object satisfies condition.

name: all
description:
Check if all values in array or object satisfy condition. Returns false if data is anything other than an array
or object.

name: anyPass
description: Check if data passes any conditions.

name: allPass
description: Check if data passes all conditions.
